section.section:
The requirements of this subsection apply if:
A clearly visible electric or mechanical signal device warns of the immediate approach or passage of a railroad train;
A crossing gate is lowered;
A flagman signals the approach or passage of a railroad train;
A railroad train approaching within 1,500 feet of the crossing gives a signal audible to traffic approaching the crossing and the railroad train, because of its speed or nearness to the crossing, is an immediate danger; or
A railroad train is plainly visible and is in or is approaching dangerously near to the crossing.
